Gratuitous:

http://www.agoranomic.org/cgi-bin/mailman/private/agora-business/2009-April/01
9041.html

The attachment purportedly used to initiate this case is readable with
no special effort - unlike, say,

http://www.agoranomic.org/cgi-bin/mailman/private/agora-business/2009-April/01
9129.html

which requires the user to recognize it as base64-encoded text.  (Note
that ehird is not the only offender of this sort.)  This second example
demonstrates that, while readability in the archive is desirable, it is
not the same as readability in one's own mail reader.

